cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with neural networks, their training, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with image classification tasks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for accelerating training, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses the MNIST dataset, which is commonly used in natural language processing tasks, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
